ney]]|archive-date=2020-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200630123035/https://money.cnn.com/2017/11/10/technology/culture/divided-we-code-alt-tech/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>许多该类平台将自己定位为[[言論自由|言論自由]]和[[公民自由|公民自由]]的保护者，往往是作为其极右翼用户群和[[反犹太主义|反犹太主义]]的掩护。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Can Alt-Tech Help the Far Right Build an Alternate Internet?|url=https://www.fairobserver.com/business/technology/alt-tech-far-right-online-extremism-hate-speech-technology-news-19919/|accessdate=2020-09-04|author=Squire|date=2019-07-23|first=Megan|authorlink=Megan Squire|work=Fair Observer|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918141929/https://www.fairobserver.com/business/technology/alt-tech-far-right-online-extremism-hate-speech-technology-news-19919/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Silverman-HoustonChronicle">{{Cite web|title=5 things to know about Parler, the right-wing-friendly social network|url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/techburger/article/5-things-to-know-about-Parler-the-15720637.php|accessdate=2020-11-12|author=Silverman|date=2020-11-12|first=Dwight|work=[[The_Houston_Chronicle|The Houston Chronicle]]|language=en-US|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114212319/https://www.houstonchronicle.com/techburger/article/5-things-to-know-about-Parler-the-15720637.php|archivedate=2020-11-14|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ADL-2020-11">{{Cite web|title=Parler: Where the Mainstream Mingles with the Extreme|url=https://www.adl.org/blog/parler-where-the-mainstream-mingles-with-the-extreme|accessdate=2020-11-14|date=2020-11-12|work=[[Anti-Defamation_League|Anti-Defamation League]]|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114212320/https://www.adl.org/blog/parler-where-the-mainstream-mingles-with-the-extreme|archivedate=2020-11-14|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="forward">{{Cite web|title=This Twitter Alternative Was Supposed To Be Nicer, But Bigots Love It Already|url=https://forward.com/news/national/427705